com.ibm.team.process.common.advice

Class ProcessRunnable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.team.process.common.advice.ProcessRunnable

  • public abstract class ProcessRunnable
extends java.lang.Object
    Runnable which is executed by the Process framework without support for advisors and participants, but which can return an operation report.

    Process runnables are commonly used when a component defines an advisable operation on the server which is not called from an advisable operation on the client. In this situation, a process runnable is defined on the client which returns the operation report from the server to the process framework.

    Unlike advisable operations, these runnables are not declared to the Process framework via the com.ibm.team.process.client or com.ibm.team.process.service configurationPoints extension-points. They are simply instantiated programatically and passed to the process framework.

    Clients may not execute a process runnable directly. Instead, they should pass the runnable to the execute methods on com.ibm.team.process.client.IProcessClientService or com.ibm.team.process.service.IProcessServerService.

    Since:
    0.6
    See Also:
    AdvisableOperation} to support advisors and participants.

      • ProcessRunnable

        public ProcessRunnable(java.lang.String operationIdentifier)
        Creates a new runnable with an operation identifier. As this runnable is not a true operation, this identifier will not be configurable in process specifications.

        Runnables can specify an operation identifier solely for the purpose of registering a detail provider factory on this id.

        Parameters:
        operationIdentifier - the operation identifier
        See Also:
        com.ibm.team.process.ide.ui.advice.IDetailProviderFactory

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public abstract IOperationReport run(org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                              throws TeamRepositoryException
        Runs this runnable and returns any advice which was computed in the course of executing the runnable or null if no advice was computed.

        Implementors of this method should check the progress monitor for cancellation when it is safe and appropriate to do so.

        This method may not be called directly by clients. Clients wishing to run this runnable should do so via the methods on the client library or server service.

        Parameters:
        monitor - the monitor used to report progress and receive cancellation requests
        Returns:
        an operation report containing any advice which was computed in the course of running the runnable or null
        Throws:
        TeamOperationCanceledException - in the event that this method caused another operation to run and that operation was canceled by process
        TeamRepositoryException - if an error occurs

      • getOperationIdentifier

        public java.lang.String getOperationIdentifier()
        Returns an operation identifier for this runnable or null if this runnable has not specified an identifier.

        Identifiers are optional for process runnables. They can be provided for the purpose of allowing a custom UI presentation to be registered.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Implementers are encouraged to provide meaningful equality for their runnables.

        A meaningful equality check allows the framework to clear old operation reports when a new report is created for the same runnable. For example, if the user attempts to save an item and is blocked by process, the next time they try to save the same item this should be identified as the same runnable (allowing the framework to remove the previous report).
